*The [[Vanyar]] and the [[Noldor]] cross the [[Blue Mountains]] and reach [[Beleriand]]. Passing over the [[Vale of Sirion]] they reach the shores of the [[Belegaer|Great Sea]] and become afraid. [[Oromë]] returns to [[Valinor]].<ref>{{AA|63}}, p. 83</ref>

==Other versions of the legendarium==
The [[Grey Annals]] date the arrival of the Noldor and Vanyar in Beleriand to 1115 and make no mention of the Second Sundering. [[Christopher Tolkien]] notes in the preface to the Annals of Aman: "The dates of the annals of the Years of the Trees were changed very frequently – in some cases there are as many as six substitutions – and I give only the final form." Thus, one of the two dates seems to be a remnant of an earlier draft.
